TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION:
SQL override is used to perform the following operation 1.Records from VRAP.TUSER_VEND_BE where a)Insert timestamp is greater than maximum timestamp of records from last successful run
2.Joining records from step 1 with VRAP.TUSER to find CORP_CD for all records
3.Cartesian product of results from step 2 and records from static table VRAP.TUSER_ASGMT_EFF_ID_LIST where USR_ASGMT_EFF_ID BETWEEN ( 20 || SUBSTR (A.STRT_PRD, 4, 2) || SUBSTR (A.STRT_PRD, 2, 2)) AND ( 20 || SUBSTR (A.END_PRD, 4, 2) || SUBSTR (A.END_PRD, 2, 2))
VRAP.TUSER_ASGMT_EFF_ID_LIST contains 1200 records the format of each record is 4 times 'Y' and 2 times 'M'.Records starts from 200001,200002 till 209912
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: SQ_Sources

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT DISTINCT A.CORP_CD AS CORP_OWNR_ID, A.USER_GID AS USR_ID, A.CO_BE_ID AS BUS_ENTY_ID, A.VEND_ID AS VNDR_ID, B.USR_ASGMT_EFF_ID AS USR_ASGMT_STRT_PRD, A.UPDT_TS, A.TUSER_UPDT_TS FROM (SELECT DISTINCT TUSER.CORP_CD, TV.USER_GID, TV.CO_BE_ID, TV.VEND_ID, TV.STRT_PRD, TV.END_PRD, TV.UPDT_TS, TUSER.UPDT_TS TUSER_UPDT_TS FROM VRAP.TUSER_VEND_BE TV INNER JOIN VRAP.TUSER TUSER ON TV.USER_GID = TUSER.USER_GID AND TV.ACTV_CD=1 WHERE (TV.UPDT_TS >TIMESTAMP('$$LOAD_LAST_INSERT_TS') OR TUSER.UPDT_TS>TIMESTAMP('$$LOAD_LAST_UPDT_TS')) ) A, VRAP.TUSER_ASGMT_EFF_ID_LIST B WHERE B.USR_ASGMT_EFF_ID BETWEEN ( 20 || SUBSTR (A.STRT_PRD, 4, 2)|| SUBSTR (A.STRT_PRD, 2, 2)) AND ( 20|| SUBSTR (A.END_PRD, 4, 2)|| SUBSTR (A.END_PRD, 2, 2)) ORDER BY A.CORP_CD , A.USER_GID , A.CO_BE_ID , A.VEND_ID, B.USR_ASGMT_EFF_ID, A.UPDT_TS, A.TUSER_UPDT_TS

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup condition
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: BUS_ENTY_ID = in_BUS_ENTY_ID AND VNDR_ID = in_VNDR_ID AND USR_ASGMT_STRT_PRD = in_USR_ASGMT_STRT_PRD
